  "event_preview": "Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya is a 4.657 km (2.894 mi) permanent road course in Montmeló, north of Barcelona. The second round of the 2026 Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup takes place June 12-14, supporting the Spanish Grand Prix. Jacques Villeneuve, the 1997 Formula One World Champion, makes his debut as a VIP guest driver at this round. The season marks the first to use the new Porsche 911 Cup based on the 992.2 generation, alongside the 25th consecutive season of Michelin as tyre supply partner.\n\nTen teams share the 28 permanent entries, with Porsche Juniors Flynt Schuring and Marcus Amand among the standout names to watch, alongside eleven Supercup newcomers making their series debuts this season. Following the season-opening race in Monaco, the field heads to Barcelona's faster, more flowing layout — a circuit that traditionally rewards strong aerodynamic efficiency and tends to produce closer racing than the tight streets of Monte Carlo.",
